               <floruit>388-420<ref type="note" corresp="#d2e12266"/>
               </floruit>
               <note xml:id="d2e12235" n="1"> On the <span xml:lang="gr"></span>
                            prefix see vol. 1, Introduction 2.1.1.2.1, p. 18. The name in Greek
                            would look as <span xml:lang="gr"></span>. On this form
                            see vol. 3, under Hananiah (7) B/M, p.
                    92.</note>
               <note xml:id="d2e12247" n="2">
                            Jerome writes in this letter to Pammachius and Oceanus that he took
                            lessons from this person late at night because Baranina was afraid of
                            what the Jews would do to him if they knew he was imparting their
                            knowledge to
                    Christians.</note>
               <note xml:id="d2e12266" n="3"> Was Jerome’s
                            teacher during his years in Bethlehem. These are the dates of his
                            sojourn there.</note>
            </person>
